The Material editor contains a display window in which you will see a
sphere. This sphere will show the user how editing changes affect the
material being applied to the selected object in Movieola. To the
right of this display are the controls of the Material Editor.

	Edit Color
	        Amb : (Slider/Field)
	        Diff : (Slider/Field)
	        Spec : (Slider/Field)
	        Emis : (Slider/Field)

	Shininess : (Slider/Field)
	Transp : (Slider/Field)

Amb : This sets the reflected color of the selected object in response
to the ambient lighting in the scene.

Diff : This sets the base color of the selected object in Movieola.

Spec : This sets the reflective quality of the selected object's
highlights.

Emis : This sets the light emitted by the selected object.

Shininess : This sets the degree of shininess of an object's surfaces,
ranging from 0.0 for a diffuse surface with no shininess to a maximum
of 1.0 for a highly polished surface..

Transp : This is the level of transparency of the object selected in
Movieola. A value of 0.0 corresponds to an opaque surface and a value
of 1.0 to a completely transparent surface.

